      "title": "Mississauga welcomes federal investment to restore the Cooksville Creek watershed",
      "summary": "The City of Mississauga is welcoming $453,406 in federal funding through the Government of Canada’s Natural Infrastructure Fund to restore and strengthen the Cooksville Creek watershed. ), helping protect one of Mississauga’s largest watersheds while improving green space for residents. Key improvements The Iggy Kaneff Park restoration project supports the City’s climate and sustainability goals while making parks more enjoyable for the community. 1 hectares), limiting the watershed’s ability to manage stormwater and flooding risks.",
